	When subprocess of /bin/sh exit(2)s with negative argument, the value of $? bacomes
	bad. (-/ instead of -1, for example)

Fix: 

BTW, should WEXITSTATUS() return unsigned value? (I don't know what POSIX says about this)--UMOTYSeGA6LKAvQzpvAilGUqfRsQkVT7qILIGT7XRR6Y1VYX
